The paper deals with dense image alignment, which is a common problem in computer vision and robotics. The use of binary descriptors is also a key aspect of the paper, which suggests that it could be relevant to the computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper proposes a novel approach that combines the robustness of binary descriptors with the speed and accuracy of dense alignment methods, which could be of interest to the multimedia (cs.MM), machine learning (cs.LG), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories.
